00:31:42,320 --> 00:31:44,234
and I tell him we should be grateful.

529
00:31:44,439 --> 00:31:45,962
First of all, it could have
been much worse.

530
00:31:46,115 --> 00:31:47,759
It could have gotten to his lungs.

531
00:31:48,010 --> 00:31:50,675
Second of all, this can't happen
to other children.

532
00:31:51,389 --> 00:31:52,759
They think they're athletes.

533
00:31:53,267 --> 00:31:54,378
I want to say to chet,

534
00:31:54,542 --> 00:31:56,779
I saw you play football
in high school,

535
00:31:57,190 --> 00:31:59,515
your son is going to be
a tackling dummy just like you.

536
00:32:11,043 --> 00:32:13,473
According to Glen here,
when the door is a little bit open

537
00:32:13,614 --> 00:32:14,988
you're supposed to come in.

538
00:32:15,816 --> 00:32:16,873
Hello, Helen.

539
00:32:17,724 --> 00:32:19,309
<i>Kelly where are you?</i>

540
00:32:19,566 --> 00:32:21,686
I hate to start with
a bunch of excuses,

541
00:32:21,838 --> 00:32:25,067
but the baby sitter was late and
I still haven't unpacked all the boxes

542
00:32:25,229 --> 00:32:27,696
so this was the only
paper I could find.

543
00:32:30,397 --> 00:32:33,203
It should be christmas all year
as far as I'm concerned.

544
00:32:37,888 --> 00:32:40,577
<i>...in New York city is expected
to receive the tax evasion...</i>

545
00:32:42,789 --> 00:32:45,172
<i>Opera's production of Mozart's</i>

546
00:32:45,503 --> 00:32:46,731
<i>Marriage of Figaro.</i>

547
00:32:47,532 --> 00:32:49,293
<i>With Meryl and Joan Sutherland.</i>

548
00:32:50,688 --> 00:32:52,861
Don, you have to pick up
the cake from hightop.

549
00:32:53,733 --> 00:32:56,493
And this is Helen Bishop and Glen.

550
00:32:56,768 --> 00:32:57,825
Nice to meet you all.

551
00:32:59,316 --> 00:33:01,049
Don, he goes with me,

552
00:33:01,690 --> 00:33:04,106
then Carlton, Chet, and Jack.

553
00:33:04,599 --> 00:33:07,018
Glen, I'm pretty sure there's some
peanut butter sandwiches

554
00:33:07,135 --> 00:33:09,871
and a bb gun out there in the
backyard. Why Don't you come with me?

555
00:33:16,536 --> 00:33:17,968
Don, can I speak with you?

556
00:33:19,616 --> 00:33:21,577
Let's see, I told you about the cake

557
00:33:21,694 --> 00:33:24,159
and, oh, can you take
some movies this time?

558
00:33:24,876 --> 00:33:26,923
Of everyone, or just chief Tiny Tim?

559
00:33:27,504 --> 00:33:29,719
You bought that camera
and you always forget.

560
00:33:30,753 --> 00:33:31,753
Okay.

561
00:33:36,777 --> 00:33:37,869
Ladies.

562
00:33:38,139 --> 00:33:39,968
Ladies. This is Helen Bishop.

563
00:33:40,955 --> 00:33:43,315
This is Maryland and Nancy.

564
00:33:44,439 --> 00:33:46,017
She seems scared, poor thing.

565
00:33:46,940 --> 00:33:50,057
Trust me, those hens are gonna
peck her to death.

566
00:33:50,483 --> 00:33:52,834
Did you see her running around
in that little Volkswagen?

567
00:33:53,089 --> 00:33:54,111
It's kinda desperate.

568
00:33:54,252 --> 00:33:56,259
Yeah that won't help her.
It's got no backseat...

569
00:33:56,353 --> 00:33:58,155
She'll have to find some
midget hitchhiker.

570
00:34:00,579 --> 00:34:02,040
Last time I saw one of those,

571
00:34:02,267 --> 00:34:04,073
I think I was throwing
a grenade into it.

572
00:34:05,662 --> 00:34:07,615
The problem with easter
break is it's too long.

573
00:34:07,915 --> 00:34:08,966
The doldrums.

574
00:34:09,137 --> 00:34:12,064
We're thinking about seven
days six nights in Boca Raton...

575
00:34:12,467 --> 00:34:14,540
With mosquitoes as
big as a silver dollar.

576
00:34:14,691 --> 00:34:16,816
And believe me, those
aren't the only giant noses

577
00:34:16,966 --> 00:34:18,326
you're going to have to deal with.

578
00:34:18,521 --> 00:34:19,560
Francine!

579
00:34:20,342 --> 00:34:22,063
Carlton and I when there
on our honeymoon

580
00:34:22,204 --> 00:34:24,090
and all I can say is
we were outnumbered.

581
00:34:24,341 --> 00:34:25,341
It's uncomfortable.

582
00:34:25,592 --> 00:34:26,900
You want to be able to relax.

583
00:34:27,152 --> 00:34:28,835
We went to Bermuda on our honeymoon.

584
00:34:28,965 --> 00:34:30,175
Pink sand beaches.

585
00:34:31,589 --> 00:34:32,911
Where did you go?

586
00:34:35,151 --> 00:34:36,549
I'm sorry.

587
00:34:38,470 --> 00:34:39,470
It's okay.

588
00:34:39,777 --> 00:34:40,777
I went to Paris.

589
00:34:41,342 --> 00:34:43,369
Four years of mount holyoke french,

590
00:34:44,715 --> 00:34:45,814
haven't used it since.

591
00:34:49,290 --> 00:34:50,461
And I wouldn't give it back,

592
00:34:50,653 --> 00:34:52,275
even being with Glen's father.

593
00:34:52,716 --> 00:34:54,191
Is that your ex-husband?

594
00:34:56,090 --> 00:34:57,090
Yes.

595
00:34:59,030 --> 00:35:00,387
I went to Italy.

596
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:01,880
Not on my honeymoon,

597
00:35:02,027 --> 00:35:03,855
right after I graduated
from Brimmare.

598
00:35:05,024 --> 00:35:06,116
What a summer.

599
00:35:06,283 --> 00:35:07,563
"Three coins in the fountain."

600
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:09,000
it was right about that time.

601
00:35:09,215 --> 00:35:10,721
You must have loved Paris.

602
00:35:10,965 --> 00:35:11,965
It's all walking.

603
00:35:12,527 --> 00:35:13,527
What do you mean?

604
00:35:13,778 --> 00:35:15,147
Just that I've seen you

605
00:35:15,465 --> 00:35:17,185
walking around the neighborhood.

606
00:35:17,825 --> 00:35:19,833
I've seen you too, when I was driving.

607
00:35:20,029 --> 00:35:21,029
I think I waved.

608
00:35:21,402 --> 00:35:22,987
Where are you going
when you do that?

609
00:35:23,274 --> 00:35:24,343
No place.

610
00:35:24,465 --> 00:35:25,465
I just like to walk.

611
00:35:29,593 --> 00:35:30,593
But where?

612
00:35:31,218 --> 00:35:32,218
Anywhere.

613
00:35:33,110 --> 00:35:34,753
It just relaxes me... clears my mind.

614
00:35:35,994 --> 00:35:37,861
I heard on the radio
that Einstein did it.

615
00:35:37,981 --> 00:35:38,991
Einstein?

616
00:35:39,159 --> 00:35:40,606
He's got his hands in everything.

617
00:35:55,848 --> 00:35:57,027
hey, daddy!

618
00:36:11,514 --> 00:36:12,837
what are you, Frank Sinatra?

619
00:36:12,970 --> 00:36:14,433
I was looking for Glen.

620
00:36:15,530 --> 00:36:17,011
Bunch of 'em just ran through.

621
00:36:21,396 --> 00:36:22,718
There are the boys.

622
00:36:23,966 --> 00:36:24,966
How we doing?

623
00:36:30,244 --> 00:36:32,014
It's, uh, it's Helen, right?

624
00:36:34,577 --> 00:36:36,232
I know your situation

625
00:36:36,767 --> 00:36:38,847
and my heart breaks
for that little boy.

626
00:36:39,329 --> 00:36:40,475
I have a baby, too.

627
00:36:41,952 --> 00:36:44,869
You can act strong,
but I just want to volunteer.

628
00:36:45,496 --> 00:36:46,600
If you ever need someone

629
00:36:46,766 --> 00:36:48,813
to throw the ball around
with him some sunday,

630
00:36:48,953 --> 00:36:50,193
take him to the beach...

631
00:36:51,267 --> 00:36:52,267
That would be nice.

632
00:36:54,283 --> 00:36:55,398
I'm sure eventually

633
00:36:55,480 --> 00:36:57,169
I would get so used
to your sunday visits

634
00:36:57,298 --> 00:36:58,644
I'd join you at the beach.

635
00:36:59,018 --> 00:37:00,352
Just the four of us.

636
00:37:01,079 --> 00:37:03,725
Then one night, you'd drop
us off at the house

637
00:37:03,910 --> 00:37:06,305
and walk me in with an umbrella.

638
00:37:06,535 --> 00:37:07,619
The kids would go to sleep

639
00:37:07,766 --> 00:37:09,974
and we'd laugh about
all the funny things

640
00:37:10,091 --> 00:37:11,830
that happened at the beach that day.

641
00:37:12,627 --> 00:37:14,153
I Don't want you telling Francine

642
00:37:14,331 --> 00:37:16,055
that I suggested
something that I didn't.

643
00:37:17,445 --> 00:37:20,334
Well, I'm sorry if I misunderstood.

644
00:38:06,232 --> 00:38:07,606
you dented the car!

645
00:38:07,791 --> 00:38:09,587
I like sleeping on the couch.

646
00:38:10,886 --> 00:38:12,271
I Don't like your tongue.

647
00:38:12,893 --> 00:38:14,250
Take your shoes off.

648
00:38:22,814 --> 00:38:24,206
I want the wagon!

649
00:38:25,889 --> 00:38:27,803
Okay, I give it to you
and then I get it.

650
00:38:28,105 --> 00:38:29,537
You're gonna hurt the baby.

651
00:38:29,889 --> 00:38:31,368
Take the baby out.

652
00:38:32,646 --> 00:38:34,243
Interesting crowd in there.

653
00:38:38,206 --> 00:38:39,692
Same crowd out here.

654
00:38:41,958 --> 00:38:43,445
How about the Einstein thing?

655
00:38:43,727 --> 00:38:46,862
I wonder if ol' Albert Swung
his hips like that when he walked.

656
00:38:47,150 --> 00:38:49,400
She probably got her
hair tips from him, too.

657
00:38:49,767 --> 00:38:50,983
Glen is so quiet.

658
00:38:51,207 --> 00:38:52,963
Not to mention wrinkled.

659
00:38:53,517 --> 00:38:55,809
Maybe she hasn't
unpacked her iron, either.

660
00:38:57,333 --> 00:38:58,538
Christmas paper?

661
00:38:59,022 --> 00:39:00,022
Please.

662
00:39:00,706 --> 00:39:01,706
She works.

663
00:39:02,208 --> 00:39:03,943
It has to be hard
to run a house, too.

664
00:39:05,043 --> 00:39:07,062
Manning a counter at a jewelry store?

665
00:39:07,521 --> 00:39:08,648
It's not that demanding.

666
00:39:08,895 --> 00:39:12,288
I Don't know. I had a job in sales
before I was a mom.

667
00:39:13,647 --> 00:39:14,983
Have you seen my mom?

668
00:39:15,828 --> 00:39:18,071
No, honey. Maybe she's
in the dining room.

669
00:39:21,647 --> 00:39:22,647
Betty?

670
00:39:22,831 --> 00:39:23,831
What?

671
00:39:37,083 --> 00:39:40,084
Don, will you please go
to hightop and get the cake?

672
00:39:53,302 --> 00:39:54,688
Don't run in the house.

673
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:56,472
What is going on in here?

674
00:39:56,836 --> 00:39:58,199
Your kid knocked over a drink.

675
00:39:58,907 --> 00:40:01,138
You need to tell him
this is not a jungle gym.

676
00:40:01,806 --> 00:40:04,847
Ernie, did you hear
what mr. Farrelly said?

677
00:40:06,380 --> 00:40:08,235
Did you say you were sorry?

678
00:40:09,262 --> 00:40:10,384
Do you want some more.

679
00:40:10,543 --> 00:40:12,022
No, come on.

680
00:40:13,209 --> 00:40:14,320
He heard me.

681
00:40:14,673 --> 00:40:17,361
Go get your mother and
have her clean this up.

682
00:40:56,295 --> 00:40:57,570
okay, thank you.

683
00:41:01,355 --> 00:41:03,527
The woman at the bakery
said he picked up the cake

684
00:41:03,692 --> 00:41:04,936
almost an hour ago.

685
00:41:06,009 --> 00:41:07,459
Do you think he had an accident?

686
00:41:07,694 --> 00:41:08,716
Let's go.

687
00:41:08,907 --> 00:41:10,466
We haven't done birthday cake.

688
00:41:10,632 --> 00:41:12,167
There's not gonna be a cake.

689
00:41:12,321 --> 00:41:13,764
Am I the only one that knows that?

690
00:41:15,884 --> 00:41:18,096
Don Draper,
you are a first class heel,

691
00:41:18,259 --> 00:41:19,510
and I salute you.

692
00:41:20,884 --> 00:41:21,899
Let's go.

693
00:41:22,197 --> 00:41:23,512
Swell party. Food was delicious.

694
00:41:31,447 --> 00:41:32,745
I might have a cake.

695
00:41:33,324 --> 00:41:34,810
A sara lee in my freezer.

696
00:41:36,587 --> 00:41:37,803
Well, could you go get it?

697
00:41:37,927 --> 00:41:39,724
Please, that would be so great.

698
00:42:07,547 --> 00:42:09,320
Happy birthday, little baby.

699
00:43:28,657 --> 00:43:29,826
Daddy!

700
00:43:38,349 --> 00:43:39,640
Mommy, mommy, look!

701
00:43:40,076 --> 00:43:41,844
Daddy got me a doggie!

702
00:43:45,014 --> 00:43:46,847
I Don't even know what to say.

703
00:43:48,012 --> 00:43:49,487
I want to name her...

704
00:43:49,617 --> 00:43:50,636
Polly!

705
00:43:50,773 --> 00:43:52,076
Polly doggie.

706
00:44:11,451 --> 00:44:13,019
Happy birthday, baby.

